#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:69
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "Gametype:"
msgstr "Vrsta igre:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "Board, Arcade"
msgstr "Igra na ploči, Arkadna igra"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "Number of possible players:"
msgstr "Mogući broj igrača:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "Four"
msgstr "Četiri"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kajongg; is a board game created after the famous oriental game of Mah Jong "
"(from Chinese <foreignphrase lang=\"zh\">麻將</foreignphrase>). It is played "
"by four players. Worldwide many different rulesets are in use. Right now "
"&kajongg; supports the Classical Chinese rules as played in Germany, "
"eventually other main rulesets will follow. It is possible to customize or "
"add new rulesets. Please do so and send them to the program author for "
"integration!"
msgstr ""
"&kajngg; je igra na ploči kreirana nakon poznate orijentalne igre Mah Jong "
"( od kkineskog <foreignphrase lang=\"zh\">麻將</foreignphrase>). Igru igraju "
"četiri igrača. Koristi se mnogo različitih pravila širom svijeta. Trenutno "
"&kajongg; podržava Klasična Kineska pravila kako se igra u Njemačkoj, a "
"ostali pravilnici prate njih. Moguće je prilagoditi ili dodati nova pravila. "
"Molimo vas uradite to i pošaljite ta pravila autoru programa zbog "
"integracije."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kajongg; can be used in two different ways: Scoring a manual game where you "
"play as always without the help of a computer and use &kajongg; for the "
"computation of scores and for bookkeeping. Or you can use &kajongg; to play "
"against any combination of other human players or computer players."
msgstr ""
"&kajongg; može da se koristi na dva načina: Ručno bodovanje igre gdje igrate "
"kao i obično bez kompjuterske pomoći i korištenjem &kajongg;-a za računanje "
"rezultata i knjigovodstvo. Ili možete &kajongg; da igrate protiv bilo koje "
"kombinacije drugog igrača ili kompjuterskog igrača."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Screen Layout"
msgstr "Izgled zaslona"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:84 index.docbook:162 index.docbook:222
#, no-c-format
msgid "A screenshot of &kajongg;"
msgstr "Slika ekrana &kajongg;-a"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:89 index.docbook:166 index.docbook:227 index.docbook:453
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot"
msgstr "Slika ekrana"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "A quick explanation of the parts of the game screen."
msgstr "Brzo objašnjenje dijelova ekrana igre."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:98
#, no-c-format
msgid "Toolbar"
msgstr "Alatna traka"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:99
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Toolbar is located beneath the menubar and contains buttons for the most "
"often used actions. The content of the Toolbar can be edited. You can also "
"make it invisible, giving more room to the Board."
msgstr ""
"Alatna traka je locirana ispod trake menija i sadrži dugmad za najčešće "
"korištene radnje. Ova stavka alatne trake se može uređivati. Možete je "
"takođe učiniti nevidljivom, dajući time više prostora ploči."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:101
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Depending on the size of your screen you may want to make the toolbar "
#| "invisible or to move it to the left side of the window. You can do that "
#| "by right-clicking with the mouse on the toolbar."
msgid ""
"Depending on the size of your screen you may want to make the toolbar "
"invisible or to move it to the left side of the window. You can do that by "
"click with the &RMB; on the toolbar."
msgstr ""
"U zavisnosti od veličine vašeg ekrana možete željeti da alatna traka bude "
"nevidljiva ili da je pomjerite na lijevu stranu prozora. To možete uraditi "
"desnim klikom mišem na alatnu traku."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "Board"
msgstr "Ploča"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Board is the largest section of the window. You see the four walls with "
"a length of 18 tiles (the exact number depends on the rules like using bonus "
"tiles or not). The names of the players are written on the walls, together "
"with the current value of the hand (as far as known) and their wind tiles. "
"The prevailing wind has a coloured background, east in the screenshot above."
msgstr ""
"Ploča je najveći dio prozora. Vidite četiri zida dužine 18 pločica ( tačan "
"broj zavisi od pravila poput dozvole korištenja bonus pločica iline ). Imena "
"igrača su napisana na zidu, zajedno sa trenutnom vrijednošću ruke ( dosad "
"poznatom ) i njhovim letećim pločicama. Preovladavajući vjetar ima obojenu "
"pozadinu, istočno na slici iznad."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When <link linkend=\"play\">playing</link>, the interior of the walls holds "
"the tiles discarded by the players. They are randomly placed. The last "
"discarded tile has a blue focus frame."
msgstr ""
"Kada <link linkend=\"play\">igrate</link>, unutrašnjost zidova sadrži "
"pločice odbačene od strane igrača. One su nasumično postavljene. Zadnja "
"odbačena pločica ima plavi fokusni okvir."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:112
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When <link linkend=\"scoreGame\">scoring manual games</link>, the interior "
"of the walls has a selection of all available tiles, the central selector. "
"You can assign them to the players using the mouse or the keyboard."
msgstr ""
"Kada je <link linkend=\"scoreGame\">dobijanje bodova manualnim igrama</"
"link>, unutrašnost zidova sadrži selekciju slobodnih pločica, centralni "
"selektor. Možete ih dodijeliti igračima korišenjem miša ili tastature."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:118
#, no-c-format
msgid "Player Region"
msgstr "Oblast za igrače"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:119
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Every player has a screen range for her tiles. The upper row contains "
"exposed tiles, the lower row concealed tiles. When <link linkend=\"scoreGame"
"\">scoring manual games</link>, concealed tiles are shown with a shadow over "
"the entire tile. Bonus tiles go to the right end."
msgstr ""
"Svaki igrač ima oblast za svoje pločice. Gornji red sadrži izložene pločice, "
"a donji red sakrivene. Kada <link linkend=\"scoreGame\">dobijanje bodova "
"manualnim igrama</link>, sakrivene pločice su prikazane sa sa sjenom preko "
"cijele pličice. Bonus pločice idu na desni kraj."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dialog"
msgstr "Dijalog"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The dialog presents choices the player has. Most often it has a timeout with "
"a progress bar showing the remaining time."
msgstr ""
"Dijalog predstavlja izbore koje ima igrač. Najčešče ima tajm-aut sa "
"progresnom trakom koja prikazuje preostalo vrijeme."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:132
#, no-c-format
msgid "Status bar"
msgstr "Statusna traka"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:133
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Status bar is located at the bottom of the screen and contains the "
"current totals for the players."
msgstr ""
"Statusna traka je locirana na dnu ekrana i sadrži trenutne totale igrača."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scoring a Manual Game"
msgstr "Dobijanje bodova Manualne igre"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this mode, &kajongg; is only used to do the scoring. You play as usual "
"with real people on a real table and at the end of a game you can tell "
"&kajongg; the tiles a player has in her hand and everything else &kajongg; "
"needs to know for calculating the scores - which is what the program will "
"do. Alternatively you can calculate the hand scores manually and enter them. "
"&kajongg; will then make the payments amongst the players and write the "
"results into a data base. It is possible to suspend a game, start another "
"game with other players and resume old games. All rules will be saved "
"together with the games, so different games can be played with different "
"rules."
msgstr ""
"U ovom modu, &kajongg; se koristi samo za bodovanje. Možete igrati kao i "
"obično sa stvarnim ljudima na stvarnoj ploči i na kraju ige možete reći "
"&kajnogg;-u koje pločice igrač ima u ruci i sve ostalo što &kajongg; treba "
"da zna za računanje rezultata- šro će program raditi. Altrenativno možete "
"ručno računati rezultate i unositi ih. &kajongg; će onda uraditi proračun "
"između igrača i napisati rezultate u bazu podataka. Moguće je prekinuti "
"igru, početi novu sa drugim igračima i nastaviti stare igre. Sva pravila će "
"biti spremljena zajedn sa igrom, pa različite igre mogu biti igrane sa "
"različitim pravilima."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:145
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "From the menu, select <guimenu>Game</guimenu> / <guimenuitem>Score Manual "
#| "Game</guimenuitem> or press <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>C</"
#| "keycap></keycombo>."
msgid ""
"From the menu, select <menuchoice><guimenu>Game</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Score "
"Manual Game</guimenuitem></menuchoice> or press <keycombo action=\"simul"
"\">&Ctrl;<keycap>C</keycap></keycombo>."
msgstr ""
"Iz menija, odaberite <guimenu>Igra</guimenu> / <guimenuitem>Bodovanje "
"manuelne igre</guimenuitem> ili pritisnite <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;"
"<keycap>C</keycap></keycombo>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:148
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you can either select an existing unfinished game or start a new game. "
"If you start a new game, you will be asked for the players and the ruleset. "
"&kajongg; will propose the same values used for the previous game. If there "
"was no previous game, it will propose the first four defined players. Please "
"note that you cannot change the ruleset or any of its rules after this "
"selection. You can do that beforehand in <link linkend=\"ruleset-options"
"\">the ruleset editor</link>."
msgstr ""
"Sada možete ili odabrati postojeću nedovršenu igru ili početi novu igru. Ako "
"počnete novu igru, bit ćete pitani za igrače i pravila. &kajongg; će "
"predložiti iste vrijednosti kao za prethodnu igru. Ako prethodne igre nema, "
"predložit će prva 4 definirana igrača. Molimo zapamtite da ne možete "
"prromijeniti pravilnik ili bilo koji od njegovih pravila nakon ovog odabira. "
"Možete to uraditi unaprijed u <link linkend=\"ruleset-options\">editor "
"pravilnika</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:151
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Now you get a new window titled \"Enter the hand results\". Read <link "
#| "linkend=\"enterhand-tiles\">Have &kajongg; compute the score</link> for a "
#| "detailed description."
msgid ""
"Now you get a new window titled <guilabel>Scoring for this Hand</guilabel>. "
"Read <link linkend=\"enterhand-tiles\">Have &kajongg; compute the score</"
"link> for a detailed description."
msgstr ""
"Sada možete dobiti novi prozor sa naslovom \"Unesite rezultate\". Pročitajte "
"<link linkend=\"enterhand-tiles\">Neka &kajongg; računa rezultat</link> za "
"detaljniji opis."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:154
#, no-c-format
msgid "After saving hand results, continue with the next hand."
msgstr "Nakon spremanja rezltata ruke, nastavite sa sljedećom rukom."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:158
#, no-c-format
msgid "Entering hand results"
msgstr "Unošenje rezultata ruke"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:160
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scores"
msgstr "Rezultati"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:169
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the window for entering hand results. It automatically shows itself "
"when &kajongg; thinks you might need it. You can always show or hide it by "
"pressing <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>S</keycap></keycombo> or "
"by selecting the corresponding menu entry."
msgstr ""
"Ovo je prozor za unos rezultata ruke. On se automatski prikazuje kada "
"&kajongg; misli da ga trebate. Možete ga uvijek prikazati ili sakriti "
"pritiskom na <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>S</keycap></keycombo> "
"ili birajući odgovarajući unos menija."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid "As always the prevailing wind has its background colored."
msgstr "Kao i uvijek preovladavajući vjetar ima svoju pozadinu obojenu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:175
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here you can manually enter scores for all players. Alternatively you can "
"exactly define which tiles a player had in her hand. If you choose to do "
"that, the corresponding field for the manual score value will be grayed out. "
"&kajongg; will automatically compute the score."
msgstr ""
"Ovje možete ručno unijete rezultate za sve igrače. Altrenativno možete tačno "
"definisati koje pločice je igrač imao u ruci. Ako to odaverete, odgovarajuće "
"polje za ručnu vrijednost rezultata će biti posivljen. &kajongg; će "
"automatski izračunati rezultat."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After having entered all relevant data for a hand, press the button "
"<guibutton>Save Hand</guibutton>. The hand values will be entered in the "
"data base, and they are also shown in the score table. You might be prompted "
"to change the seating positions of the players but you can choose not to "
"change seats. The proposed changes are currently not customizable - if a "
"ruleset needs something different, we will change that."
msgstr ""
"Nakon unosa svih relevantnih podataka za ruku, pritinsite dugme "
"<guibutton>Spremi ruku</guibutton>. Vrijednosti ruke će biti uneseni u bazu "
"podataka, i takođe su prikazani u tabeli rezultata. Možete biti pitani za "
"promjenu rasporeda sjedenja igrača ali možete izabrati da ih ne mijenjate. "
"Tražene promjene trenutno nisu podesive - ako pravilnik bude trebao nešto "
"drugačije, promijenit ćemo to."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:181
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If the player might have won, the check box in the column \"Winner\" will "
#| "be enabled - click this for the winner."
msgid ""
"If the player might have won, the check box in the column <guilabel>Winner</"
"guilabel> will be enabled - click this for the winner."
msgstr ""
"Ako je igrač pobijedio, kutija za označavanje u koloni \"Pobjednik\" će biti "
"omogućen - klinkite ovo za pobjednika."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:184
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The status bar will now show the updated balances for the players, and you "
"can continue with the next hand."
msgstr ""
"Statusna traka će sada prikazati ažurirane informacije za igrače, i onda "
"možete nastaviti na sljedeću ruku."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enter the score manually"
msgstr "Unesite rezultat ručno"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:189
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A good player will probably prefer to compute her score himself. In that "
"case you can directly enter it. This is only possible when no tiles are "
"selected for this player."
msgstr ""
"DObar igrač će vjerovatno preferirati da računa rezultat samostalno. U tom "
"slučaju možete ih direktno unijeti. Ovo je moguće samo ako nijedna pločica "
"nije odabrana za ovog igrača."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:192
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you enter a manual score, it must already contain everything except "
#| "penalties, you will have no optional rules to choose from. There is one "
#| "exception: \"Dangerous Game\". This does not influence any scores, it is "
#| "no offense either. It only means the payment between players is "
#| "different: The offender pays all for all to the winner. The other two "
#| "players do not exchange payments. This is currently not customizable."
msgid ""
"If you enter a manual score, it must already contain everything except "
"penalties, you will have no optional rules to choose from. There is one "
"exception: <quote>Dangerous Game</quote>. This does not influence any "
"scores, it is no offense either. It only means the payment between players "
"is different: The offender pays all for all to the winner. The other two "
"players do not exchange payments. This is currently not customizable."
msgstr ""
"Ako uneste rezultat ručno, oni moraju da već sadrže sve osim penala, nećete "
"imati opcionalna pravila za biranje. Jedan je izuzetak : \"Opasna igra\". "
"Ovo ne utiče na rezultate, niti je prekršaj. Samo znači da je naplata između "
"igrača drugačiji.  Prekršitelj plaća sve pobjedniku. Druga dva igrača ne "
"razmjenjuju naplate. Ovo trenutno nije podešivo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:197
#, no-c-format
msgid "Have &kajongg; compute the score"
msgstr "Neka &kajongg; računa rezultat"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:198
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you explicitly tell &kajongg; what tiles a player holds, entering scores "
"will be grayed out for that player in this window. While associating tiles "
"with a player you will see how her score will grow - but as soon as you add "
"the 14th tile the score goes to zero. That might surprise you but unless you "
"declare this as the winner hand, it is recognized as a long hand which "
"always has zero points. This behaviour is defined by the Classical Chinese "
"ruleset, it might be different if you change the rules or use a different "
"ruleset."
msgstr ""
"Ako eksplicitno kažete &kajongg;-u koje pločice igrač drži, uns rezultata će "
"posivjeti za igrača na ovom prozoru. Prilikom povezivanja pločica sa igračem "
"vidjet ćete kako negov rezultat raste - ali čim dodate 14. pločicu rezultata "
"pada na nulu. Ovo vas može iznenaditi ali osim ako deklarišete ovo kao "
"pobjedničku ruku, to je prepoznato kao preduga ruka što uvijek dobija nula "
"poena. Ovo ponašanje je definisano Klasičnim Kineskim pravilnikom, može biti "
"drugačije ako promijenite pravilo ili koristite drugi pravilnik."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:201
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can associate tiles and melds with a player using either the mouse or "
"the keyboard or both. With the mouse simply move tiles by dragging/dropping "
"them to the player region. When dropping the tile, you will be asked what "
"you want to move: Single, Pair, Pung, Kong, Claimed Kong or Chow. The upper "
"row is for exposed tiles, the lower row for concealed tiles. The bonus tiles "
"will appear to the far right. You can also move tiles and melds between "
"rows, between players and back to the central selector."
msgstr ""
"Možete povezati pločice i miješati sa igračem korištenjem ili miša ili "
"tastature ili oboje. Sa mišem jednostavno pomjerate pločice povlačeći/"
"ispuštajuči ih na oblast igrača. Pri ispuštanju pločice bit ćete pitani šta "
"želite pomjeriti : Jednu pločicu, Par, Pung, Kong, Claimed Kong ili Chow. "
"Gornji red je za izložene pločice, donji za sakrivene pločice. Bonus pločice "
"će se prikazati skroz desno. Možete takođe pomjerati pločice i miješati "
"između redova, između igrača i nazad u centralni selektor."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:204
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you prefer using the keyboard, you can use &Tab; to move between the "
#| "central selector and the player regions. The keys <keycap>eswnESWN</"
#| "keycap> move a tile to the players East, South, West and North. The keys "
#| "<keycap>xX</keycap> move it back to the central selector. <keycap>ESWN</"
#| "keycap> moves to the concealed row, <keycap>eswn</keycap> moves to the "
#| "exposed row. You can move the cursor between tiles or melds using the "
#| "arrow keys, the currently selected tile or meld has a blue frame. Since "
#| "the key arrows are far away from letters on the keyboard, you can also "
#| "use the letters <keycap>hjkl</keycap> or <keycap>HJKL</keycap> for moving "
#| "the cursor. <keycap>hH</keycap> move left, <keycap>jJ</keycap> move down, "
#| "<keycap>kK</keycap> move up, <keycap>lL</keycap> move right. This is how "
#| "the unix editor \"vi\" does it. The &kde; browser konqueror and even this "
#| "help program also support those keys in the same way. Those keys may "
#| "differ if you use a language other than English but it is currently not "
#| "possible to configure them."
msgid ""
"If you prefer using the keyboard, you can use &Tab; to move between the "
"central selector and the player regions. The keys <keycap>eswnESWN</keycap> "
"move a tile to the players East, South, West and North. The keys <keycap>xX</"
"keycap> move it back to the central selector. <keycap>ESWN</keycap> moves to "
"the concealed row, <keycap>eswn</keycap> moves to the exposed row. You can "
"move the cursor between tiles or melds using the arrow keys, the currently "
"selected tile or meld has a blue frame. Since the key arrows are far away "
"from letters on the keyboard, you can also use the letters <keycap>hjkl</"
"keycap> or <keycap>HJKL</keycap> for moving the cursor. <keycap>hH</keycap> "
"move left, <keycap>jJ</keycap> move down, <keycap>kK</keycap> move up, "
"<keycap>lL</keycap> move right. This is how the unix editor <command>vi</"
"command> does it. The &kde; browser &konqueror; and even this help program "
"also support those keys in the same way. Those keys may differ if you use a "
"language other than English but it is currently not possible to configure "
"them."
msgstr ""
"Ako preferirate tastaturu, možete koristiti &Tab; da pomjerate između "
"centralnog selektora i oblasti igrača. Tipke  <keycap>eswnESWN</keycap> "
"pomjeranje pločice igračima Istočno, Južno, Zapadno i Sjeverno. Tipke "
"<keycap>xX</keycap> pomjeraju ih nazad u centralni selektor. <keycap>ESWN</"
"keycap>  pomjera skriveni red, <keycap>eswn</keycap> pomjera izloženi red. "
"Možete pomjeriti kursor između pločica koristeći tipke sa strelicama, "
"trenutno odabrana pločica ima plavi okvir. Kako su tipke sa strelicama "
"daleko od slova na tastaturi, možete takođe koristiti slova <keycap>hjkl</"
"keycap>  ili <keycap>HJKL</keycap> za pomjeranje kursora. <keycap>hH</"
"keycap> pomjera lijevo, <keycap>jJ</keycap> pomjera dolje, <keycap>kK</"
"keycap> pomjera gore, <keycap>lL</keycap> pomjera desno. Ovo je kako unix "
"editor \"vi\" to radi. &kde; pretraživac konqueror ili čak ovaj pomoćni "
"pgroram podržava te tipke na isti način. Te tipe mogu se razlikovati ako "
"koristite jezik koji nije Engleski ali trenutno nije ih moguće konfigurisati."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:211
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The options \"Last Tile\" and \"Last Meld\" are needed by some rules like "
#| "\"last tile completes pair\". They can only be used for the winner hand."
msgid ""
"The options <guilabel>Last Tile:</guilabel> and <guilabel>Last Meld:</"
"guilabel> are needed by some rules like <guilabel>Last tile completes pair</"
"guilabel>. They can only be used for the winner hand."
msgstr ""
"Opcije \"Posljednja pločica\" i \"Posljednje miješanje\" su potrebne za neka "
"pravila kao \"posljenjda pločica završava par\". One takođe mogu biti "
"korištene za pobjedničku ruku."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:214
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In the right part of the window you can manually apply some rules. What "
#| "rules appear in this list depends on the current ruleset and on the "
#| "tiles. In the example of the above screen shot, the losing players might "
#| "have an option \"dangerous game\" - again depending on the ruleset and on "
#| "their tiles. It is the aim of the developers to keep this list of "
#| "manually selectable rules as short as possible. Optimally &kajongg; "
#| "should always be able to automatically determine whether a rule applies, "
#| "but sometimes &kajongg; does not have enough information or knowledge to "
#| "decide."
msgid ""
"In the right part of the window you can manually apply some rules. What "
"rules appear in this list depends on the current ruleset and on the tiles. "
"In the example of the above screen shot, the losing players might have an "
"option <quote>dangerous game</quote> - again depending on the ruleset and on "
"their tiles. It is the aim of the developers to keep this list of manually "
"selectable rules as short as possible. Optimally &kajongg; should always be "
"able to automatically determine whether a rule applies, but sometimes "
"&kajongg; does not have enough information or knowledge to decide."
msgstr ""
"Na desnom dijelu prozora možete ručno primijeniti neka pravila. Koje se "
"pravilo pojavi na listi zavisi od trneutnog pravilnika i pločica. U primjeru "
"iznad slike ekrana, igrač koji gubi može imati opciju \"opasna igra\"- što "
"opet zavisi od pravilnika i njegovih pločica. Cilj je razvijača da drše ovu "
"listu za ručno biranje pravila što je kraće moguće. Optimalno &kajongg; bi "
"trebao uvijek biti u mogučnosti da automatski odredi da li da primijeni "
"pravilo, ali nekada &kajongg; nema dovoljno informacija ili znanja da odluči."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid "Penalties"
msgstr "Kazne"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:230
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <link linkend=\"enterhand\">window for entering hand results</link>, "
"the <guibutton>Penalties</guibutton> button will bring up this window where "
"you can enter penalties. This can be done at any point in time independent "
"of the normal scoring mechanism."
msgstr ""
"Na linku <link linkend=\"enterhand\">prozoru za unos rezultata ruke</link>, "
"<guibutton>Kazne</guibutton> dugme će otvoriti prozor gdje možete unijeti "
"kazne. Ovo može da se odradi u bilo kojem trenutku neovisno od normalnog "
"mehanizma bodovanja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:232
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The <guilabel>Offense</guilabel> selection shows all offenses that might "
#| "be applicable to the hands the players hold. Choose among them."
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Offense:</guilabel> selection shows all offenses that might be "
"applicable to the hands the players hold. Choose among them."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Prekršaj</guilabel> selekcija prikazuje sve prekršaje koji mogu "
"biti primjenjivi na ruke koje igrači drže. Izaberite između njih."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:233
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you can adapt the <guilabel>Total Penalty</guilabel>. This is the total "
"sum that is moved from payers to payees. It will be evenly split between "
"them."
msgstr ""
"Sada možete prilagoditi <guilabel>Totalna kazna</guilabel>. Ovo je totalna "
"suma koja je pomjerena od onih koji plaćaju do onih koji primaju. Bit će "
"jednako podijeljena između njih."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:234
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Depending on the type of offense, the number of payers and payees varies. "
"The right number of players is displayed. If you select a player, &kajongg; "
"ensures that this player only occurs once by adapting the other players."
msgstr ""
"U zavisnosti od tipa prekršaja, broj onih koji plaćaju i onih koji primaju "
"se mijenja. Tačan broj igrača je prikazan. Ako odabere igrača , &kajongg; da "
"se ovaj igrač desi samo jednom prilagođavajući ostale igrače."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid "Playing"
msgstr "Igranje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:241
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At any time, you can enable or disable the Demo Mode. In Demo Mode, the "
"computer will play for you. If no game is currently played, a new game will "
"be started with the last used ruleset."
msgstr ""
"U bilo koje vrijeme, možete uključiti ili isključiti Demo mod. U Demo modu, "
"kompjuter igra za vas. Ako nijedna igra nije trenutno igrana, nova igra će "
"početi po zadnjem korištenom pravilniku."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:245
#, no-c-format
msgid "Play against the computer"
msgstr "Igra protiv kompjutera"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:246
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "First you will get a login dialog. Enter the game server you want to "
#| "connect to and your user name. If you choose the special entry \"Local "
#| "Game\", you only need to enter your name (or accept the proposed name) "
#| "and the wanted ruleset. This will immediately start a local game where "
#| "you play against 3 robot players. However if suspended games exist, they "
#| "will be displayed in a list. You can then select the game you want to "
#| "continue with or start a new game."
msgid ""
"First you will get a login dialog. Enter the game server you want to connect "
"to and your user name. If you choose the special entry <guilabel>Local Game</"
"guilabel>, you only need to enter your name (or accept the proposed name) "
"and the wanted ruleset. This will immediately start a local game where you "
"play against 3 robot players. However if suspended games exist, they will be "
"displayed in a list. You can then select the game you want to continue with "
"or start a new game."
msgstr ""
"Prvo će se otvoriti dijalog za logovanje. Unesite server igre na koji se "
"želite konektovati i vaše korisničko ime. Ako odabere poseban unos \"Lokalna "
"igra\", trebat ćete unijeti vaše ime ( ili prihvatiti predloženo ime) i "
"željeni pravilnik. Ovo će trenutačno pokrenuti lokalnu igru gdje igrate "
"protiv 3 igrača robota. Međutim ako prekinute igre postoje, bit će prikazane "
"na listi. Možete onda odabrati igru koju želite nastaviti ili pokrenuti novu "
"igru."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:254
#, no-c-format
msgid "Play with friends"
msgstr "Igra sa prijateljima"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:255
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to play against other real people, you need a game server to "
"which all players, including yourself, need to connect. Do that by selecting "
"any other host or by manually entering a new host name and by specifying "
"your password for that host. The last used password will be proposed."
msgstr ""
"Ako želite da igrate protiv stvarnih ljudi, treba vam server igre na koji se "
"svi igrači, uključujući vas, trebaju konektovati. Uradite to selektujući "
"drugi host ili ručno unoseći novo ime hosta i navodeći šifru za taj host. "
"Bit će vam predložena posljednja korištena šifra."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:259
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The easiest way is to use the game server at <ulink url=\"http://www.kde."
#| "org/applications/games/kajongg/\">kajongg.org</ulink>. &kajongg; will "
#| "show this one in the list of possible game servers. Please note that for "
#| "now <ulink url=\"http://www.kde.org/applications/games/kajongg/\">kajongg."
#| "org</ulink> only offers a game server but no web page or any other "
#| "services."
msgid ""
"The easiest way is to use the game server at <literal>kajongg.org</literal>. "
"&kajongg; will show this one in the list of possible game servers. Please "
"note that this server only offers a game server but no web page or any other "
"services."
msgstr ""
"Najjednostavniji način je da koristite server igre na<ulink url=\"http://www."
"kde.org/applications/games/kajongg/\">kajongg.org</ulink>. &kajongg; će "
"prikazati ovaj server u listi mogućih servera igre. Molimo vas zapamtite da "
"za sada <ulink url=\"http://www.kde.org/applications/games/kajongg/"
"\">kajongg.org</ulink> nudi samo server za igru ali ne i web stranicu ili "
"neku drugu uslugu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:262
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you do not have an account on the game server with the name you entered, "
"you will be asked if you want to open an account. If you say yes, you will "
"get a new dialog where you can enter the wanted password twice. Your account "
"will be created automatically."
msgstr ""
"Ako nemate račun na serveru igre sa imenom koji ste unijeli, bit ćete pitani "
"da li želite otvoriti račun. Ako kažete da, novi dijalog će se otvoriti gdje "
"možete unijeti željenu šifru dva puta. Račun će se automatski kreirati."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:265
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After a successful login onto the game server, you will get a list of tables "
"with available seats on that game server. Join a table or allocate a new "
"table. If you allocate a new table, wait until more seats are taken by other "
"players. You can start the game on a table you allocated at any time, the "
"seats not taken will be filled by robot players."
msgstr ""
"Nakon uspješnog prijavljivanja na server igre, dobit ćete listu stolova sa "
"dozvoljenim mjestima na tom serveru igre. Pridružite se stolu ili alocirajte "
"novi sto. Ako alocirate novi sto, čekajte da drugi igrači zauzmu mjesta. "
"Možete početi igru na stolu koji ste alocirali bili kada, a mjesta koja nisu "
"zauzeta će biti popunjena od strane robota."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:269
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The table list also shows the name of the ruleset played on that table. The "
"ruleset and its name are sent to the game server by the player initiating "
"the table. If you have an identical ruleset, the table shows your name for "
"the ruleset - this might be helpful if the table initiator speaks another "
"language and named the ruleset differently. Also, if the name of your local "
"ruleset is displayed, it is displayed in black. If however you have no "
"identical ruleset, the name appears in red, and you can use the button "
"<guibutton>Compare</guibutton> to compare it with your own rulesets."
msgstr ""
"Lista stolova takođe prikazuje naziv pravilnika igranih na tom stolu. "
"Pravilnik i njegv nazim su poslani serveru igre od strane irača koji stvara "
"sto. Ako nemate vaš jedinstveni pravilnik, sto pokazuje naziv pravilnika - "
"ovo može biti korisno ako stvaraoc stola priča drugi jezik i naziva "
"pravilnik drugačije."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:274
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you do not use <ulink url=\"http://www.kde.org/applications/games/"
#| "kajongg/\">kajongg.org</ulink> or any other existing game server, you can "
#| "start your own &kajongg; game server in two different ways:"
msgid ""
"If you do not use <literal>kajongg.org</literal> or any other existing game "
"server, you can start your own &kajongg; game server in two different ways:"
msgstr ""
"Ako ne koristite  <ulink url=\"http://www.kde.org/applications/games/kajongg/"
"\">kajongg.org</ulink> ili neki drugi postojeći server igre, možete "
"pokrenuti &kajongg; server igre na dva različita načina:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:276
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "connect to the server \"localhost\". This is your own computer. If you do "
#| "this and no game server is running, it will be started automatically. And "
#| "when you stop playing, the server will be stopped too."
msgid ""
"connect to the server <literal>localhost</literal>. This is your own "
"computer. If you do this and no game server is running, it will be started "
"automatically. And when you stop playing, the server will be stopped too. "
"This differs from selecting <guilabel>Local Game</guilabel>, the latter does "
"not allow connections from other computers."
msgstr ""
"konektujte se na server \"lokalni host\". OVo je vaš razčunar. Ako ovo "
"uradite i nijedan server za igru nije pokrenut, ovaj će biti pokrenut "
"automatski. Kada prestanete igrati i server će biti prekinut takođe."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:279
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "manually start a server on any computer you want. All you need to do is "
#| "go to a command line and start the program <literal>kajonggserver</"
#| "literal>. Entering <literal>kajonggserver --help</literal> will show you "
#| "all available options like changing the default port. This server will "
#| "run until you kill it."
msgid ""
"manually start a server on any computer you want. All you need to do is go "
"to a command line and start the program <command>kajonggserver</command>. "
"Entering <command>kajonggserver --help</command> will show you all available "
"options like changing the default port. This server will run until you kill "
"it."
msgstr ""
"ručno pokrenite server na bilo kojem računaru. Sve što trebate uraditi je da "
"odete na komandnu liniju i pokrenete program  <literal>kajonggserver</"
"literal>. Otvarajući  <literal>kajonggserver --help</literal>  pokaza će vam "
"se dozvoljene opcija kao što je promjena zadanog porta. Ovaj server će biti "
"pokrenut sve dok ga ne uništite."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:284
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In both cases you need to tell the other players how they can reach your "
#| "game server. They need the &URL; or simply an IP address and the port "
#| "your server is listening on. This might be something like <literal>mypc."
#| "dyndns.org:8409</literal> where <literal>8409</literal> is the port. Of "
#| "course you need to configure your firewall such that the remote player "
#| "can reach that port. The communication will be encrypted."
msgid ""
"In both cases you need to tell the other players how they can reach your "
"game server. They need the &URL; or simply an IP address and the port your "
"server is listening on. This might be something like <literal>mypc.dyndns."
"org:8301</literal> where <literal>8301</literal> is the port. Of course you "
"need to configure your firewall such that the remote player can reach that "
"port. The communication will be encrypted."
msgstr ""
"U oba slučaja morate da kažete drugim igračima kako da dođu do vašeg "
"servera. Oni trebaju &URL; ili jednostavno IP adresu, i port koji vaš server "
"sluša. Ovo može biti nešto kao <literal>mypc.dyndns.org:8409</literal> gdje "
"je port <literal>8409</literal>. Naravno trebate konfigurisati vašu zaštitu "
"tako da igrači mogu da dođu do porta. Ova komunikacije će biti kodirane."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:288
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The server computes its default port from its version number. If "
#| "&kajongg; has version 4.9.5, port 8409 will be used: 8000 plus first "
#| "version digit * 100 plus middle version digit. If the player enters no "
#| "port for the wanted game server, the client computes the port in the same "
#| "way. So if a computer runs several game servers with different program "
#| "versions, you should normally reach the correct game server "
#| "automatically. Anyway the game server and the client will make sure that "
#| "their versions are compatible and warn you otherwise."
msgid ""
"For the port number, please see <menuchoice><guimenu>Help</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>About &kajongg;</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. The Protocol "
"version is the port number. For &kajongg; 17.04 this is 8301. If the player "
"enters no port for the wanted game server, the client computes the port in "
"the same way. So if a computer runs several game servers with different "
"protocol versions, you should normally reach the correct game server "
"automatically. Anyway the game server and the client will make sure that "
"their versions are compatible and warn you otherwise."
msgstr ""
"Server računa zadani port iz broja njegove verzije. Ako je &kajongg;  "
"verzije 4.9.5, bit će korišten port 8409: 900 plus prva cifra vezije*100 "
"plus srednja cifra verzije. Ako igrač ne unese port a željeni server, "
"klijent računa port na isti način. Tako da ako kompjuter pokreće nekoliko "
"servera sa različitim programskim verzijama, trebali biste normalno doći do "
"tačnog servera automatski. U svakom slučaju server i klijent će sa "
"sigurnošću utvrditi da li su njihove verzije kompatibilne i upozoriti vas "
"ako nisu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:293
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you encounter possible bugs, you might want to use the option "
#| "<literal>--debug=traffic</literal>. This will show you, on the console "
#| "where the game server has been started, what messages are flowing between "
#| "the game server and the clients."
msgid ""
"If you encounter possible bugs, you might want to use the option "
"<command>kajongg --debug=traffic</command>. This will show you, on the "
"console where the game server has been started, what messages are flowing "
"between the game server and the clients. For more options, see "
"<command>kajongg --help</command>"
msgstr ""
"Ako naiđete na moguće greške, možete koristiti opciju <literal>--"
"debug=traffic</literal>. Ovo će vam pokazati na konzoli gdje je server igre "
"započet, koje poruke lete između servera i klijenta."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:298
#, no-c-format
msgid "Caveats"
msgstr "Upozorenja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:299
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to make sure nobody can cheat none of the human players should "
"have access to the computer the game server is running on. Of course you can "
"never avoid that two players help each other because you cannot know what "
"they really are doing. Two players might even be one and the same person."
msgstr ""
"Ako želite biti sigurni da niko ne može varati niko od igrača ne bi trebao "
"imati pristup kompjuteru na kojem je server pokrenut. Naravno nikada ne "
"možete izbjeći da dva igrača pomažu jedan drugome zato što ne možete znati "
"šta oni zapravo rade. Dva igrača bi mogla biti i ista osoba."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:304
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game rules"
msgstr "Pravila igre"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Worldwide, many different game variants exist. Currently, &kajongg; supports "
"two variants of Classical Chinese, one as played in Germany and one as "
"played in Great Britain."
msgstr ""
"Širom svijeta, mnogo različitih varijanti igre postoje. Trenutno, &kajongg; "
"podržava dvije varijante Klasične Kineske, ona koja se igra u Njemačkoj i "
"ona koja se igra u Velikoj Britaniji."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This description does not go into details and as such matches both variants."
msgstr "Opis ne ide u detalje i kao takva ona odgovara za obje varijatne."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:306
#, no-c-format
msgid "However most of the basic rules are the same in most variants."
msgstr "Većina osnovnih pravila su ista u obje varijante."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:308
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since the program &kajongg; knows how to play, this description only "
"contains things that might not be obvious."
msgstr ""
"Kako program &kajongg; zna kako da igra, ovaj opis sadrži samo one stvari "
"koje nisu očigledne."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:309
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to learn Mah Jong in more detail, please consult the <link "
"linkend=\"bibliography\">bibliography</link>."
msgstr ""
"Ako želite da naučite Mah Jong detaljnije, molimo konsultujte se sa <link "
"linkend=\"bibliography\">bibliography</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:311
#, no-c-format
msgid "The aim of the game"
msgstr "Cilj igre"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:312
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Each player tries to collect tiles such that she has a winning hand. On "
#| "achieving this, she calls \"Mah Jong\". In a winning hand, the tiles are "
#| "normally grouped into five melds: Four melds with three or four tiles "
#| "each and a fifth meld consisting of two equal tiles. A normal meld has "
#| "three or four identical tiles (called Pung and Kong respectively) or "
#| "three successive tiles like Bamboo 3, Bamboo 4, Bamboo 5 (called Chow)."
msgid ""
"Each player tries to collect tiles such that she has a winning hand. On "
"achieving this, she calls <quote>Mah Jong</quote>. In a winning hand, the "
"tiles are normally grouped into five melds: Four melds with three or four "
"tiles each and a fifth meld consisting of two equal tiles. A normal meld has "
"three or four identical tiles (called Pung and Kong respectively) or three "
"successive tiles like Bamboo 3, Bamboo 4, Bamboo 5 (called Chow)."
msgstr ""
"Svaki igrač pokušava da sakupi pločice tako da ima pobjedničku ruku. Kada "
"ovo postigne, poziva \"Mah Jong\". U pobjedničkoj ruci, pločice su normalno "
"grupisane u pet grupa: Četiri grupe sa po tri ili četiri pločice i peta koja "
"sadrži dvije iste ploičice. Normalna grupa sadrži tri ili četiri pločice "
"( nazvane Pung i Kong respektivno ) i tri sukcesivne pločice kao Bamboo 3, "
"Bamboo 4, Bamboo 5 ( nazvan Chow)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:317
#, no-c-format
msgid "The course of the game"
msgstr "Tok igre"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:318
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Initially, the player with the East wind (as indicated on the wall) has one "
"more tile than the other players. East begins by discarding an unwanted tile."
msgstr ""
"Inicijalno, igrač na Istočnoj strani (kao što je pokazano na zidu ) ima "
"jednu više pločicu od ostalih igrača. Istočni igrač počinje odbacujuči "
"neželjenu pločicu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:321
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whenever a tile has been discarded, other players can claim it by saying "
"what they can complete with that tile (Chow, Pung, Kong, Mah Jong). Only the "
"next player can claim a Chow - the other claims are possible for all "
"players. A meld completed by a claim will be exposed - made visible to all "
"players."
msgstr ""
"Kad god je pločica odbačena, drugi igrači je mogu zatražiti govoreči da mogu "
"zavržiti sa tom pločicom ( Chow, Pung, Kong, Mah Jong). Samo sljedeći igrač "
"može zatražiti Chow - a ostali mogu zatražiti za ostale. Grupa dovršena zbog "
"ovog zahtjeva će biti izložena - postati vidljiva svim igračima."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:325
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If nobody claims the discarded tile, the next player, South (and then West "
"and North) gets a tile from the wall and discards an unwanted tile."
msgstr ""
"Ako niko ne zatraži odbačenu pločicu, sljedeći igrać, Jug ( pa onda Zapad i "
"Sjever ) dobija pločicu sa zida i odbacuje neželjenu pločicu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:327
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are several rules about when a Pung can be extended to a Kong (by "
"claiming the forth tile or by getting it from the wall) - these rules are "
"not explained here. But &kajongg; of course knows them and makes sure they "
"are respected. If a Kong is declared, the player automatically gets a "
"replacement tile from the wall - otherwise it would not be possible to build "
"the five melds as mentioned above."
msgstr ""
"Postoje određena pravila o tome kada Pung može postati Kong ( tražeći "
"četvrtu pločicu ili dobijajuči je sa zida) - ova pravila nisu objašnjena "
"ovdje. Ali  &kajongg; naravno zna to i osigurava da je to uvaženo. Ako je "
"Kong proglašen, igrač automatski dobija zamjenu pločice sa zida - inače ne "
"bi bilo moguće da se pravi grupa od 5 pločica kao što je navedeno iznad."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:333
#, no-c-format
msgid "Year, Round and Hand"
msgstr "Godina, Krug i Ruka"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:333
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When a player claims Mah Jong or we end up in a draw, a hand is completed. "
"Now, except for draws, the winds rotate among the players. This is repeated "
"until every player once had every wind. This entire unit is called a round. "
"An entire game, also called year, consists of four such rounds: East wind "
"round, South wind round, West wind round, North wind round. The wind of a "
"round is also called prevailing wind, it can result in higher scores."
msgstr ""
"Kada igrač traži Mah Jong ili završimo nerješeno, ruka je završena. Sada, "
"osim za nerješeno, strane se rotiraju između igrača. Ovo se ponavlja sve dok "
"svaki igrač nije imao svaku stranu. Cijela jedinica je nazvana krug. Cijela "
"igra, nazvana i godina, sadrži četiri takva kruga. Istočni krug, Južni krug, "
"Zapadni krug, Sjeverni krug. Strana kruga je takođe nazvana preovladavajuća "
"strana i može rezultovati višim rezultatom."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:338
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"So a full game (a year) consists of at least 16 hands. Since the winds do "
"not rotate for draws or when the East player says Mah Jong, a higher number "
"of hands is normally needed for a full game."
msgstr ""
"Pa cijela igra ( godina ) sadrži najmanje 16 ruku. Kako se strane ne "
"rotiraju za izvlaćenje ili kad Istočni igrač kaže Mah Jong, viši broj ruku "
"ruku je potreban za cijelu igru."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:340
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bonus tiles"
msgstr "Bonus Pločice"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:341
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A game can contain eight bonus tiles (unless the rules exclude them). They "
"are exposed separately on the right side of the player region as they are "
"never used for building melds. They do however generate bonus points."
msgstr ""
"Igra može da sadrži osam bonus pločica (osim ako su pravilima isključene). "
"One su izložene odvojeno na desnoj strani dijela za igrače kako nikad nisu "
"korištene za stvaranje grupa. Međutim one generišu bonus poene."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:343
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If a player gets a bonus tile, she will automatically also get a "
#| "replacement tile from the wall."
msgid ""
"If a player gets a bonus tile, she will automatically also get a replacement "
"tile from the wall. And a bell rings."
msgstr ""
"Ako igrač dobije bonus pločicu, automatski dobija i zamjenu pločice sa zida."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scoring"
msgstr "Bodovanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At the end of a hand, the score for each player is computed. First, basis "
"points are counted like 2 points for a simple exposed pung or 20 points for "
"winning. Next, another set of rules is applied - those rules can double the "
"points like one double for a meld of dragons. When the score for each hand "
"is known, differences are paid between players - while the winner gets its "
"full score paid from all other players. East always gets and pays twice her "
"score."
msgstr ""
"Na kraju ruke, rezltat za svakog igrača je izračunat. Prvo, bazni poeni su "
"računati kao 2 poena za izloženi pung ili 20 poena za pobjedu. Dalje, drugi "
"skup pravila je primijenjen - ova pravila mogu duplati poene kao duplanje za "
"grupu zmajeva. Kada je rezltat za svaku ruku poznat, razlike su isplaćene "
"između igrača - dok pobjednik dobija puni rezultat isplaćen od svih drugih "
"igrača. Istočni igrač dobija i plaća dva puta njegov rezultat."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:349
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Of course &kajongg; knows about all applicable rules but a good player knows "
"what combinations get what score so she can optimize. While learning it is "
"recommended to activate the window <guimenuitem>Explain Scores</guimenuitem>."
msgstr ""
"Naravno &kajongg; zna sve o primijenjivim pravilima ali dobar igrać zna šta "
"nose koje kombinacije pa može optimizirati igru. Tokom učenja preporučeno je "
"aktivirati prozor <guimenuitem>Objasni rezultat</guimenuitem>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:351
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The exact scoring rules often vary - in &kajongg; you are free to change "
"them with the <link linkend=\"ruleset-options\">the ruleset editor</link>."
msgstr ""
"Tačna pravila bodovanja variraju - u &kajongg; -u slobodni ste da "
"promijenite pravila sa <link linkend=\"ruleset-options\">editorom "
"pravilnika</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:352
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The ruleset editor also shows you all available rules and their meaning. "
"Place the mouse over them and for the more exotic rules help text will "
"appear."
msgstr ""
"Editor pravilnika takože pokazuje sva dozvoljena pravila i njihova značenja. "
"Stavite miš preko njih i za egzotičnija pravila pomoćni tekst će se pojaviti."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:357
#, no-c-format
msgid "How to play with &kajongg;"
msgstr "Kako igrati sa &kajongg;-om"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:358
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You will be prompted for what you want to do. This is a little dialog which "
"appears either on the right or at the bottom depending on the size of the "
"window. If you make it broader than high, the dialog appears on the right. "
"Sometimes the dialog will have a timeout - when it is over, the first "
"possible answer is automatically selected for you. This timeout is "
"configurable in the Ruleset Editor, under <guilabel>Options</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Claim Timeout</guilabel>. All players should have the same "
"timeout, that is why this is part of the ruleset."
msgstr ""
"Bit ćete pitani šta želite raditi. Ovo je mali dijalog koji se pojavljuje "
"ili desno ili na dnu u zavisnosti od veličine prozora. Ako je širi više nego "
"viši, dijalog se pojavljuje desno. Nekada dijalog ima tajm-aut - kada je "
"završen, prvi mogući odgovor je automatski selektovan za vas. Ovaj tajm-aut "
"je moguće konfigurisati u Editoru pravilnika, ispod <guilabel>Opcije</"
"guilabel>, <guilabel>Zatraži tajm-aut</guilabel>.Svi igrači bi trebali imati "
"isti tajm-aut, i zbog toga je ovo dio pravilnika."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:363
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you need to select a tile from your hand, you can move between tiles "
#| "using the right and left arrow keys or the letters h and l on your "
#| "keyboard. Of course you can use the mouse too."
msgid ""
"If you need to select a tile from your hand, you can move between tiles "
"using the &Right; and &Left; arrow keys or the letters <keycap>h</keycap> "
"and <keycap>l</keycap> on your keyboard. Of course you can use the mouse too."
msgstr ""
"Ako trebate odabrati pločicu iz ruke, možete se pomjerati između pločica "
"koristeći strelicu lijevo i desno ili slova h i l na vašoj tastaturi. "
"Naravno možete koristiti i miš."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:365
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can discard a tile by using the keyboard the same way as for all "
"actions. Alternatively, you can use the mouse and move the tile from your "
"hand into the discard area (the interior of the walls). The placement of the "
"tile in the discard area will still be done by the computer - because the "
"placement should be the same for players."
msgstr ""
"Možete odbaciti pločicu koristeći tastaturu na isti način kao i sve radnje. "
"Altrenativno možete koristiti miš i pomjerati pločicu iz vaše ruke u prostor "
"za odbacivanje ( unutrašnost zidova). Smještaj pločice u oblasti za "
"izbacivanje odrađuje kompjuter - zato što je smještaj isti za sve igrače."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:369
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Often, the dialogs will offer choices which are not really applicable like "
"calling Pung when you do not have the needed tiles. This is intended - just "
"like in a real game. But you can configure impossible choices away: Disable "
"<guilabel>Show only possible actions</guilabel> on the <guilabel>Play</"
"guilabel> page of the settings dialog."
msgstr ""
"Često dijalog će vam pnuditi opcije koje nisu zaista primjenjive kao "
"pozivanje Punga kada nemate potrebne pločice. Ovo je namjerno - baš kao u "
"stvarnoj igri. Ali možete konfigurisati nemoguće izbore : Onemogući "
"<guilabel>Prikaži samo moguće opcijce</guilabel> na <guilabel>Igraj</"
"guilabel> stranici dijaloga postavki."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:372
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Discarded tiles are placed randomly between the walls. Some game variants "
"define where the tiles should be placed, this is not yet configurable "
"however. When it becomes configurable, it will be part of the ruleset."
msgstr ""
"Odbačene pločice su smještene nasumično između zidova. Neke varijante igre "
"definišu gdje se trebaju smjestiti pločica, što još uvijek nije podesivo. "
"Kada postane podesivo, bit će dio pravilnika."

