#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:545
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game Configuration"
msgstr "Konfiguracija igre"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:548
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Configure Dialog</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Konfiguracijski dijalog</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:554
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Configure Dialog</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Konfiguracijski dijalog</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:559
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The menu entry <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>Configure &kajongg;...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> "
#| "opens the <guilabel>Configure - &kajongg;</guilabel> dialog."
msgid ""
"The menu entry <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Configure &kajongg;...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> opens the "
"<guilabel>Configure - &kajongg;</guilabel> dialog."
msgstr ""
"Unos menija  <menuchoice><guimenu>Postavke</guimenu><guimenuitem>Konfiguriši "
"&kajongg;...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> otvara  <guilabel>Konfiguracijski - "
"&kajongg;</guilabel> dijalog."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:560
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you press the <guibutton>Cancel</guibutton> button here, all of your "
"configuration changes will be reverted, including everything you did with "
"the ruleset editor."
msgstr ""
"Ako pritisnete <guibutton>Izlaz</guibutton> dugme ovdje, sve vaše "
"konfiguracijske promjene će biti vraćene, uključujući i sve što ste radili "
"sa editorom pravilnika."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:561
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also select the different tabs with the keyboard: <keycombo action="
"\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>1</keycap></keycombo> selects the first tab "
"<guilabel>Play</guilabel> options, <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;"
"<keycap>2</keycap></keycombo> selects the second tab, and so on."
msgstr ""
"Možete takođe odabrati različite tabove sa tastaturom: <keycombo action="
"\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>1</keycap></keycombo> selektuje prvi tab "
"<guilabel>Pokreni</guilabel> opcije, <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;"
"<keycap>2</keycap></keycombo> selektuje drugi tab, i tako dalje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:567
#, no-c-format
msgid "Play options"
msgstr "Opcije igre"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:571
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show tile shadows"
msgstr "Pokaži sjene pločica"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:573
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This shows tiles with borders and shadows. Also there is some space between "
"tile rows, and the wall tiles are shown such that you can see that the wall "
"is two or three tiles high. So if you disable this option, you have a "
"simpler display with slightly larger tiles. This may be helpful for small "
"screens."
msgstr ""
"Ovo prikazuje pločice sa granicama i sjenama. Takođe postoji prostor između "
"redova pločica, i zid pločica je prikazan na način da možete vidjet da je "
"zid dvije ili tri pločice visok. Tako da ako onemogućite ovu opciju, imate "
"jednostavniji prikaz sa nešto većim pločicama. Ovo može biti korisno za male "
"ekrane."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:581
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rearrange undisclosed tiles to melds"
msgstr "Preuredi neotkrivene pločice promješanim kartama"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:583
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This groups melds in the hand. Sometimes the grouping might not be like you "
"want it, so you might prefer to have no grouping at all, just like in a real "
"world game."
msgstr ""
"Ovo grupiše grupe pločica u ruci. Ponekad grupisanje nije onako kakvim ga "
"želite, pa biste možda radije željeli da ne postoji ta opcija, kao što je "
"nema u igri u stvarnom svijetu."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:590
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show only possible actions"
msgstr "Pokaži samo moguće radnje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:592
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "When playing, show only possible actions like \"No claim\" or \"Pung\"."
msgid ""
"When playing, show only possible actions like <quote>No claim</quote> or "
"<quote>Pung</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Dok igrte, prikazuje samo moguće radnje kao \"Nema zahtjeva\" ili \"Pung\"."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:598
#, no-c-format
msgid "Propose what to do"
msgstr "Predložite sta da radim"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:600
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whenever you have a choice of actions like claiming a tile or not or like "
"choosing which tile to discard, &kajongg; can help you by making a proposal."
msgstr ""
"Kada god imate izbor akcija kao što su da li da tražite kartu ili ne ili "
"koju pločicu izbaciti, &kajongg; vam može pomoći dajući vam prijedlog."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:606
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use sounds if available"
msgstr "Koristi zvuk ako je moguće"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:608
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This lets you hear discards and claims. If other players recorded sound "
"files with their own voice, you can hear them."
msgstr ""
"Ovo vam omogućava da čujete odbacivanja i zahtjeve. Ako su drugi igrači "
"snimili zvučne datoteke njihovog glasa, možete ih čuti."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:614
#, no-c-format
msgid "Let others hear my voice"
msgstr "Dopusti drugima da čuju moj glas"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:616
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you recorded sound files with your voice this option will let the other "
"players hear your discards and claims with your voice."
msgstr ""
"Ako snimite zvučne datoteke vašeg glasa ova opcija dozvoljava drugim "
"igračima da čuje vaša odbacivanja i zahtjeve sa vašim glasom."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:623
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Animation speed"
msgid "Animation speed:"
msgstr "Brzina animacije"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:625
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Define how fast the tiles should move around. If you move the slider to the "
"rightmost position, tile movement is not animated: the tiles will simply "
"change place."
msgstr ""
"Definišite kako brzo bi pločice trebale da se kreću. Ako pomjerite klizač u "
"najdesniju poziciju, kretanje pločica nije animirano, pločice će jednostavno "
"samo promijeniti poziciju."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:632
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sound"
msgstr "Zvuk"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:633
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Playing gives you a much nicer experience if you hear players claim tiles "
"and announce discards. It also makes playing easier because you can "
"concentrate on your own tiles, you do not have to watch what others discard."
msgstr ""
"Igranje vam daje mnogo ljepše iskustvo ako čujete igrače kako traže pločice "
"i najavljuju odbacivanje. Takođe, čini igranje lakšim zato što se možete "
"koncentrisati na vaše pločice bez potrebe da gledate šta drugi odbacuju."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:637
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&kajongg; comes with voices for different players. It automatically "
#| "assigns voices to players. For every language there should be four "
#| "voices, preferably two male and two female. &kajongg; tries to use voices "
#| "in the same language &kajongg; runs in. If it finds no voices in that "
#| "language, &kajongg; will fallback to other languages, using the same "
#| "fallback languages you defined for &kajongg; (see "
#| "<menuchoice><guimenu>Help</guimenu><guimenuitem>Switch Application "
#| "Language</guimenuitem></menuchoice>). If no voice files exist yet for "
#| "your language, you are invited to record and contribute them to &kajongg;."
msgid ""
"&kajongg; comes with voices for different players. It automatically assigns "
"voices to players. For every language there should be four voices, "
"preferably two male and two female. &kajongg; tries to use voices in the "
"same language &kajongg; runs in. If it finds no voices in that language, "
"&kajongg; will fallback to other languages, using the same fallback "
"languages you defined for &kajongg; (see <menuchoice><guimenu>Help</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Switch Application Language</guimenuitem></menuchoice>). If no "
"voice files exist yet for your language, you are invited to record and "
"contribute them to &kajongg;."
msgstr ""
"&kajongg; dolazi sa glasovima za različite igrače. Automatski dodjeljuje "
"glasove igračima. Za svaki jezik trebalo bi da posoje 4 glasa, dva ženska i "
"dva mušla. &kajongg; pokušava da koristi glasove na istom jeziku na kojemu "
"je &kajongg; pokrenut. Ako ne pronađe glasove na tom jeziku, &kajongg; će se "
"povući do ostalih jezika, koristeći  jezike koji ste definisali za &kajongg; "
"(pogledajte  <menuchoice><guimenu>Pomoć</guimenu><guimenuitem>Promijeni "
"jezik aplikacije</guimenuitem></menuchoice>). Ako ne postoje glasovne "
"datoteke na vašem jeziku, pozivamo vas da ih snimite i doprinesete &kajongg;-"
"u."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:645
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "This is how you can generate voices yourself. There is a separate folder "
#| "for every voice. There are two groups of voices with different places in "
#| "the file system:"
msgid ""
"This is how you can generate voices yourself. There is a separate folder for "
"every voice. Please note that those folders may be somewhere else on your "
"system, they depend on how &kde; was installed. Only the part starting with "
"<filename class=\"directory\">kajongg</filename> is always the same. There "
"are two groups of voices with different places in the file system:"
msgstr ""
"Ovo je način kako da generišete vaše glasove. Postoji odvojeni folder za "
"svaki glas. Dvije su grupe glasova sa različitim mjestima u sistemu:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:650
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Predefined voices for every language. They live in a folder like "
#| "<filename class=\"directory\">/usr/share/kde4/apps/kajongg/voices/LANG</"
#| "filename> where LANG is the code for your language. The voice directories "
#| "directly under <filename class=\"directory\">.../kajongg/voices/</"
#| "filename> are the US-english versions. Predefined voices are randomly "
#| "assigned to players. Those voices have names like <literal>\"male1 male2 "
#| "female1 female2\"</literal> but those names do not matter, the user will "
#| "never see them. Also, it makes no sense to define more than four "
#| "predefined voices per language."
msgid ""
"Predefined voices for every language. They live in a folder like <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/usr/share/kajongg/voices/LANG</filename> where LANG is "
"the code for your language. The voice directories directly under <filename "
"class=\"directory\">.../kajongg/voices/</filename> are the US-english "
"versions. Predefined voices are randomly assigned to players. Those voices "
"have names like <quote><literal>male1 male2 female1 female2</literal></"
"quote> but those names do not matter, the user will never see them."
msgstr ""
"Predefinirani glasovi za svaki jezik. Oni se nalaze u folderu kao  <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/usr/share/kde4/apps/kajongg/voices/LANG</filename>gdje "
"je LANG kod za vaš jezik. Direktoriji glasova direktno ispod  <filename "
"class=\"directory\">.../kajongg/voices/</filename> su US-engleske vezije. "
"Predifinirani glasovi su nasumično dodijeljeni igračima. Ovi glasovi imaju "
"imena kao <literal>\"male1 male2 female1 female2\"</literal> ali imena nisu "
"bitna, igrači ih nikad neće vidjeti. Takođe nema smisla definisati više od "
"četiri glasa po jeziku."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:654
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "User voices can be defined for a specific user. If &kajongg; makes use of "
#| "such a voice, it can automatically be transferred to other players over "
#| "the internet. Those voices live in a folder like <filename class="
#| "\"directory\">~/.kde/share/apps/kajongg/voices/</filename>. So if your "
#| "login name is joe, this might be <filename class=\"directory\">/home/joe/."
#| "kde/share/apps/kajongg/voices/joe/</filename>. The folder <filename class="
#| "\"directory\">voices/</filename> might not yet exist - if so, create it."
msgid ""
"User voices can be defined for a specific user. If &kajongg; makes use of "
"such a voice, it can automatically be transferred to other players over the "
"internet. Those voices live in a folder like <filename class=\"directory"
"\">~/.local/share/apps/kajongg/voices/</filename>. So if your login name is "
"joe, this might be <filename class=\"directory\">/home/joe/.local/share/apps/"
"kajongg/voices/joe/</filename>. The folder <filename class=\"directory"
"\">voices/</filename> might not yet exist - if so, create it."
msgstr ""
"Korisnički glas može biti definisan za specifičnog korisnika. Ako &kajongg; "
"iskoristi taj glas, može biti automatski proslijeđen drugim igračima širom "
"interneta. Ti se glasovi nalaze u folderu kao <filename class=\"directory"
"\">~/.kde/share/apps/kajongg/voices/</filename>. Tako da ako je vaše ime pod "
"kojim se prijavljujete joe, ovo može biti direktorij <filename class="
"\"directory\">/home/joe/.kde/share/apps/kajongg/voices/joe/</filename>. "
"Folder <filename class=\"directory\">voices/</filename> može biti "
"nepostojeći, pa ako je tako, napravite ga."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:662
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now that you know where to place your new voice, generate a new folder for "
"it."
msgstr ""
"Sada kada znate gdje da smjestite vaš novi glas, napravite novi folder za "
"njega."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:664
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In that subfolder, you can place the sound files. They have to be encoded "
#| "with the <ulink url=\"http://xiph.org/vorbis/\">Ogg Vorbis</ulink> audio "
#| "compressor, the file names need to have the extension <filename class="
#| "\"extension\">.ogg</filename>. A single file has a name like <filename>s3."
#| "ogg</filename> - this is Stone 3. You should define such files for all "
#| "tiles and for all claims and announcements. But if a sound file is "
#| "missing, nothing bad happens - you just will not hear that sound. "
#| "Fallback to other voices or languages only works for entire voices, not "
#| "for single sound files."
msgid ""
"In that subfolder, you can place the sound files. They have to be encoded "
"with the <ulink url=\"https://xiph.org/vorbis/\">Ogg Vorbis</ulink> audio "
"compressor, the file names need to have the extension <filename class="
"\"extension\">.ogg</filename>. A single file has a name like <filename>s3."
"ogg</filename> - this is Stone 3. You should define such files for all tiles "
"and for all claims and announcements. But if a sound file is missing, "
"nothing bad happens - you just will not hear that sound. Fallback to other "
"voices or languages only works for entire voices, not for single sound files."
msgstr ""
"U tom podfolderu možete smjestiti zvučne datoteke. Oni moraju biti kodirani "
"sa  <ulink url=\"http://xiph.org/vorbis/\">Ogg Vorbis</ulink>  audio "
"kompresorom, imena datoteka moraju da imaju ekstenziju <filename class="
"\"extension\">.ogg</filename>.  Jedinstvena datoteka ima ime kao "
"<filename>s3.ogg</filename> - ovo je Stone 3. Trebali biste definisati takve "
"datoteke za sve pločice i sve zahtjeve i najave. Ali ako zvučna datoteka "
"nedostaje, ništa loše se neće desiti - samo nećete čuti taj zbuk. Vraćanje "
"na druge glasove ili jezike radi samo za cijele glasove, ne za pojedinačne "
"zvučne datoteke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:670
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After having defined all sound files for a predefined voice, please make "
"sure that the &kajongg; process has write permission in the new voice "
"folder. Start &kajongg; and test the voice. After everything is OK, you can "
"revoke write permission (and you should do so for predefined voices). "
"&kajongg; will automatically generate a file named <filename>md5sum</"
"filename> containing a checksum over all sound files. Whenever you change, "
"add or delete a sound file for a voice, &kajongg; will try to rewrite that "
"file."
msgstr ""
"Nakon što ste definisali sve zvučne datoteke za predefinirani glas, molimo "
"uvjerite se da &kajongg;  proces ima dozvolu za pisanje u novom folderu "
"zvukova. Pokrenite &kajongg; i testirajte glas. Ako je sve OK, možete "
"ukinuti dozvolu za pisanje ( a to biste i trebali uraditi za predefinirane "
"glasove). &kajongg; će automtaski generisati datoteku nazvanu "
"<filename>md5sum</filename> koja sadrži sumu provjere svih zvučnih datoteka. "
"Kad god promienite dodate ili izbrišete zvučnu datoteku za glas, &kajongg; "
"će pokušati da ponovo napiše tu datoteku."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:676
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Please make the length of the sound short but speak clearly - this game can "
"be played very fast when you get used to it. It is easier if you first write "
"down a list with everything that should be spoken. Do not read it as a "
"sequence of items, try to pronounce each item as if it were the only one and "
"as you would when playing. Leave room between the items. Reading this needs "
"a little practicing."
msgstr ""
"Molimo vas da dužina zvuka bude kratka ali izgovorena jasno - ova igra može "
"da se igra jako brzo kada se naviknete na nju. Lakše je da prvo napišete "
"listu svega što treba da bude izgovoreno. Nemojte čitati listu kao niz "
"stavki, pokušajte izgovarati svaku stavku posebno kao da je jedina tu i "
"onako kako biste izgovarali dok igrate. Ostavite prostora između stavki. "
"Čitanje ovoga treba malo vježbe."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:680
#, no-c-format
msgid "This is just one possibility to create the sound files:"
msgstr "Ovo je samo jedna mogućnost pravljenja zvučnih datoteka:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:682
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Record a sound file with the program <command>qarecord</command>, save it "
#| "in the <literal>WAV</literal> format. In this single sound file, speak "
#| "all of the sounds."
msgid ""
"Record a sound file with the program <command>qarecord</command>, save it in "
"the <acronym>WAV</acronym> format. In this single sound file, speak all of "
"the sounds."
msgstr ""
"Snimite zvučnu datoteku sa programom <command>qarecord</command>, spremita "
"je u  <literal>WAV</literal> formatu. U ovom jednom zvučnom fajlu, "
"izgovorite sve zvukove."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:685
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Edit that file with the sound editor <command>audacity</command>. In that "
#| "editor, use the mouse to mark a range of the sound waves. The editor will "
#| "play that part. Repeat until you have the correct part selected. This may "
#| "be easier if you <menuchoice><guimenu>View</guimenu><guimenuitem>Zoom In</"
#| "guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Use the menu command "
#| "<menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Export Selection</"
#| "guimenuitem></menuchoice> and save in the ogg format. Under "
#| "<guilabel>Options</guilabel>, choose low quality - this is sufficient and "
#| "even wanted because this reduces the time to transfer the sounds to the "
#| "other players."
msgid ""
"Edit that file with the sound editor <command>audacity</command>. In that "
"editor, use the mouse to mark a range of the sound waves. The editor will "
"play that part. Repeat until you have the correct part selected. This may be "
"easier if you <menuchoice><guimenu>View</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Zoom In</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Use the menu command <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Export Selection</guimenuitem></menuchoice> and save "
"in the <filename class=\"extension\">.ogg</filename> format. Under "
"<guilabel>Options</guilabel>, choose low quality - this is sufficient and "
"even wanted because this reduces the time to transfer the sounds to the "
"other players."
msgstr ""
"Uredite tu datoteku sa editorom zvuka <command>audacity</command>. U ovom "
"editoru koristite miš da označite rang zvučnih talasa. Editor će pokrenuti "
"taj dio. Ponavljajte sve dok niste odabrali tačan dio. Ovo može biti lakše "
"ako <menuchoice><guimenu>Prikaz</guimenu><guimenuitem>Uvećaj</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>. Koristite komandu menija <menuchoice><guimenu>Datoteka</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Izvezite selekciju</guimenuitem></menuchoice> i "
"spremite u ogg formatu.Pod<guilabel>Opcije</guilabel> izaberite nizak "
"kvalitet - to je dovoljno i takođe poželjno zato što skraćuje vrijeme "
"prolijeđivanja zvuka drugim igračima."

